<hr data-start="230" data-end="233">
<h1 data-section-id="18bhdux" data-start="235" data-end="265">📘 README.md (FINAL VERSION)</h1>
<div class="group relative my-4 w-full overflow-visible"><div id="writing-block-4bcbfe4d-7f8f-4613-877e-8fc0a67e646f" class="relative w-full overflow-clip rounded-[24px] bg-token-bg-primary dark:bg-[#2a2a2a] shadow-[0px_4px_80px_rgba(0,0,0,0.02)]" data-writing-block="true" data-testid="writing-block-container"><div class="z-1 md:sticky top-(--sticky-padding-top)" data-testid="writing-block-header-sticky-container"><div class="bg-token-bg-primary flex w-full items-center justify-between gap-3 font-sans dark:bg-[#2a2a2a] py-2.5" data-testid="writing-block-header-surface" style="padding-left: calc(5 * var(--spacing)); padding-right: calc(1 * var(--spacing));"><div class="flex grow gap-3 items-center"><div class="text-token-text-tertiary flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 grow cursor-default items-center self-center text-sm font-medium"><div class="truncate">Writing</div></div></div><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center"><div class="flex items-center"><button class="gap-1 select-none text-sm font-medium text-token-text-primary hover:bg-token-bg-tertiary flex size-9 items-center justify-center rounded-full p-1.5 transition-colors disabled:opacity-40 disabled:hover:bg-transparent" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div></div><div class="writing-block-editor markdown-new-styling relative flow-root pt-(--writing-block-editor-pt) pe-(--writing-block-editor-pr) pb-(--writing-block-editor-pb) ps-(--writing-block-editor-pl)" style="--writing-block-editor-pt: 0px; --writing-block-editor-pr: calc(5 * var(--spacing)); --writing-block-editor-pb: calc(4 * var(--spacing)); --writing-block-editor-pl: calc(5 * var(--spacing));"><div contenteditable="true" aria-disabled="false" dir="auto" translate="no" class="ProseMirror markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full min-h-6 break-words focus:outline-none"><h1><span>🐾 PawPal+</span></h1><p><span>PawPal+ is a smart pet care management system that helps pet owners organize and prioritize daily responsibilities such as feeding, walking, medications, and appointments.</span></p><p><span>Built using Python and object-oriented programming (OOP), PawPal+ combines clean system design with algorithmic scheduling logic and an interactive Streamlit interface.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>🚀 Features</span></h2><h3><span>🐶 Pet &amp; Task Management</span></h3><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Add multiple pets under one owner</span></p></li><li><p><span>Assign tasks with time and frequency (once, daily, weekly)</span></p></li><li><p><span>Track task completion status</span></p></li></ul><h3><span>⏰ Smart Scheduling</span></h3><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Automatically sorts tasks by time</span></p></li><li><p><span>Displays a clean daily schedule</span></p></li></ul><h3><span>🔍 Filtering</span></h3><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Filter tasks by:</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Pet name</span></p></li><li><p><span>Completion status</span></p></li></ul></li></ul><h3><span>🔁 Recurring Tasks</span></h3><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Daily and weekly tasks regenerate automatically after completion</span></p></li></ul><h3><span>⚠️ Conflict Detection</span></h3><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Detects tasks scheduled at the same time</span></p></li><li><p><span>Provides warnings instead of breaking the system</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>🧠 System Architecture</span></h2><p><span>The system is built using four main classes:</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><strong><span>Task</span></strong><span> → Represents an individual activity</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Pet</span></strong><span> → Stores pet details and task list</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Owner</span></strong><span> → Manages multiple pets</span></p></li><li><p><strong><span>Scheduler</span></strong><span> → Handles sorting, filtering, recurrence, and conflicts</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>🖥️ How to Run the Project</span></h2><h3><span>1. Run CLI Demo</span></h3><pre dir="ltr"><code dir="ltr"><span>python main.py</span></code></pre><h3><span>2. Run Streamlit App</span></h3><pre dir="ltr"><code dir="ltr"><span>streamlit run app.py</span></code></pre><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>🧪 Testing PawPal+</span></h2><p><span>Run the automated test suite with:</span></p><pre dir="ltr"><code dir="ltr"><span>python -m pytest</span></code></pre><h3><span>✅ Tests Cover:</span></h3><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Task completion behavior</span></p></li><li><p><span>Adding tasks to pets</span></p></li><li><p><span>Sorting correctness</span></p></li><li><p><span>Conflict detection</span></p></li><li><p><span>Recurring task generation</span></p></li></ul><p><strong><span>Confidence Level:</span></strong><span> ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (5/5)</span><br><span>All core features are tested and working reliably.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>📸 Demo</span></h2><p><span>(Add your screenshot here)</span></p><pre dir="ltr"><code dir="ltr"><span>&lt;a href="/course_images/ai110/your_screenshot.png" target="_blank"&gt;
  &lt;img src='/course_images/ai110/your_screenshot.png' title='PawPal App' width='' alt='PawPal App' /&gt;
&lt;/a&gt;</span></code></pre><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>🧩 Smarter Scheduling</span></h2><p><span>PawPal+ includes algorithmic improvements that make it more than a simple task list:</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Uses Python’s </span><code dir="ltr"><span>sorted()</span></code><span> with lambda functions for efficient time-based ordering</span></p></li><li><p><span>Implements lightweight conflict detection using hash maps</span></p></li><li><p><span>Automates recurring tasks using </span><code dir="ltr"><span>datetime</span></code><span> and </span><code dir="ltr"><span>timedelta</span></code></p></li><li><p><span>Keeps logic modular through a dedicated </span><code dir="ltr"><span>Scheduler</span></code><span> class</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>📦 Tech Stack</span></h2><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Python</span></p></li><li><p><span>Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)</span></p></li><li><p><span>Streamlit</span></p></li><li><p><span>Pytest</span></p></li></ul><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>👩‍💻 Author</span></h2><p><span>Elizabeth Kilroy</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><p><br class="ProseMirror-trailingBreak"></p></div></div><div aria-hidden="true" class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 z-2 rounded-[24px] shadow-[inset_0px_0px_0px_1px_rgba(0,0,0,0.07)]"></div></div></div>
<hr data-start="2730" data-end="2733">
<h1 data-section-id="zwk6tr" data-start="2735" data-end="2769">🧠 reflection.md (FINAL VERSION)</h1>
<div class="group relative my-4 w-full overflow-visible"><div id="writing-block-4bcbfe4d-7f8f-4613-877e-8fc0a67e646f" class="relative w-full overflow-clip rounded-[24px] bg-token-bg-primary dark:bg-[#2a2a2a] shadow-[0px_4px_80px_rgba(0,0,0,0.02)]" data-writing-block="true" data-testid="writing-block-container"><div class="z-1 md:sticky top-(--sticky-padding-top)" data-testid="writing-block-header-sticky-container"><div class="bg-token-bg-primary flex w-full items-center justify-between gap-3 font-sans dark:bg-[#2a2a2a] py-2.5" data-testid="writing-block-header-surface" style="padding-left: calc(5 * var(--spacing)); padding-right: calc(1 * var(--spacing));"><div class="flex grow gap-3 items-center"><div class="text-token-text-tertiary flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 grow cursor-default items-center self-center text-sm font-medium"><div class="truncate">Writing</div></div></div><div class="flex shrink-0 items-center"><div class="flex items-center"><button class="gap-1 select-none text-sm font-medium text-token-text-primary hover:bg-token-bg-tertiary flex size-9 items-center justify-center rounded-full p-1.5 transition-colors disabled:opacity-40 disabled:hover:bg-transparent" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div></div><div class="writing-block-editor markdown-new-styling relative flow-root pt-(--writing-block-editor-pt) pe-(--writing-block-editor-pr) pb-(--writing-block-editor-pb) ps-(--writing-block-editor-pl)" style="--writing-block-editor-pt: 0px; --writing-block-editor-pr: calc(5 * var(--spacing)); --writing-block-editor-pb: calc(4 * var(--spacing)); --writing-block-editor-pl: calc(5 * var(--spacing));"><div contenteditable="true" aria-disabled="false" dir="auto" translate="no" class="ProseMirror markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full min-h-6 break-words focus:outline-none"><h1><span>PawPal+ Reflection</span></h1><h2><span>1. Design Decisions</span></h2><h3><span>a. System Structure</span></h3><p><span>I designed PawPal+ using four main classes: Task, Pet, Owner, and Scheduler. This separation allowed each class to have a clear responsibility. The Scheduler acts as the “brain” of the system, handling all logic such as sorting, filtering, recurrence, and conflict detection, while the other classes focus on storing data.</span></p><h3><span>b. Why This Design Works</span></h3><p><span>This modular structure makes the system easier to extend and debug. For example, adding new scheduling features does not require modifying the Pet or Owner classes, only the Scheduler.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>2. Algorithms &amp; Tradeoffs</span></h2><h3><span>a. Algorithms Implemented</span></h3><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Sorting tasks using Python’s </span><code dir="ltr"><span>sorted()</span></code><span> with a lambda function</span></p></li><li><p><span>Filtering tasks by pet name and completion status</span></p></li><li><p><span>Conflict detection using a dictionary to track time collisions</span></p></li><li><p><span>Recurring task generation using </span><code dir="ltr"><span>datetime</span></code><span> and </span><code dir="ltr"><span>timedelta</span></code></p></li></ul><h3><span>b. Tradeoffs</span></h3><p><span>One key tradeoff is in conflict detection. The system only checks for exact time matches (e.g., 08:00 vs 08:00) rather than overlapping time ranges. This simplifies the implementation and keeps the system fast and readable, but it does not catch more complex scheduling conflicts.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>3. AI Collaboration Strategy</span></h2><h3><span>a. Most Useful AI Features</span></h3><p><span>VS Code Copilot was most helpful for:</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Generating class scaffolding and method structures</span></p></li><li><p><span>Suggesting Pythonic implementations (like lambda sorting)</span></p></li><li><p><span>Creating initial test cases with pytest</span></p></li></ul><h3><span>b. AI Suggestion I Modified</span></h3><p><span>One suggestion from AI was to combine multiple responsibilities into a single class for simplicity. I chose not to follow this and instead kept the Scheduler separate to maintain clean architecture and separation of concerns.</span></p><h3><span>c. Use of Separate Chat Sessions</span></h3><p><span>Using separate chat sessions for different phases (design, implementation, testing) helped me stay organized and focused. It prevented confusion and made it easier to refine specific parts of the system.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><h2><span>4. What I Learned</span></h2><p><span>Working as the “lead architect” taught me that AI is a powerful assistant, but not a replacement for decision-making. I had to evaluate AI suggestions critically and decide what best fit my design goals.</span></p><p><span>I also learned the importance of:</span></p><ul data-spread="false"><li><p><span>Planning system architecture before coding</span></p></li><li><p><span>Testing early and often</span></p></li><li><p><span>Keeping code modular and readable</span></p></li></ul><p><span>Overall, this project showed me how to effectively collaborate with AI while maintaining control over design and quality.</span></p><div contenteditable="false"><hr></div><p><br class="ProseMirror-trailingBreak"></p></div></div><div aria-hidden="true" class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 z-2 rounded-[24px] shadow-[inset_0px_0px_0px_1px_rgba(0,0,0,0.07)]"></div></div></div>
